    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="898"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24596/4–2947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u.s. urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-19T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 19, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>582. You many inform Roxas that although Article 13<note n="18" xml:id="d898fn18"
                        >Reference is to the agreement on military bases signed March 14.</note>
                    gives United States exclusive jurisdiction “in time of war” and United States is
                    now legally at war this Government has no intention of claiming such
                    jurisdiction as it was not understanding of parties to agreement that Article
                    13(6) should apply during present war.</p>
                <p>Dept does not consider that this has any bearing on or is a precedent for lease
                    case mentioned your 687, Apr. 29<note n="19" xml:id="d898fn19">Not
                        printed.</note> since question in that case is what was intention of parties
                    to lease contract.</p>
                <p>Pass to Army and Navy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
